               <msPart xml:id="p2">
                  <msIdentifier/>
                  <msContents>
                     <summary>Ff. 3-6 containing the miniatures, unruled (only a frame on the leaves
                        with miniatures), of smaller or irregular size. In fact it is not 100% sure
                        that the miniatures were prepared and infixed into the text block later,
                        separately. The miniatures were painted by a professional artist; I see a
                        tacket in the fold above, between f. 4v and f. 5r. Another explanation
                        cannot be excluded: the quire with miniatures was bound together with
                        regular quires, and the tacket was left by chance. There is a little bit of
                        speculation, and it is a matter of interpretation (to understand better, one
                        would need to have the books in the hands) but from the point of view of
                        systematics it is better to register the leaves with miniature as a separate
                        codicological/production unit. There is a number of books where miniatures
                        (written on unruled leaves) similarly build a separate unit, the result of a
                        separate production process. </summary>
                     <msItem xml:id="p2_i1">
                        <locus from="43ra" to="52rb" facs="044"/>
                        <title>Collection of miracles </title>
                        <msItem xml:id="p2_i1.1">
